---
const steps = [
  { num: "01", color: "text-cy-300", ring: "ring-cy-300/15", heading: "Install on your Mac" },
  { num: "02", color: "text-cy-400", ring: "ring-cy-400/20", heading: "Scan the QR" },
  { num: "03", color: "text-kind-idle", ring: "ring-kind-idle/20", heading: "Walk away" },
];
---
<section class="bg-ink-900 py-28 lg:py-32">
  <div class="section">
    <span class="eyebrow ring-cy-400/25">
      <span class="eyebrow-dot bg-cy-400"></span>
      <span class="text-cy-400">60-SECOND SETUP</span>
    </span>
    <h2 class="heading-lg mt-5 max-w-[1100px]">One installer. One QR. You're paired.</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-[840px] text-[17px] leading-[1.55] text-mute-fg">
      Page signs itself with your Apple Developer cert, asks for the permissions it
      actually needs, and gets out of the way. No account. No cloud sync. Your tokens
      live on your devices.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-12 grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-3">
      <!-- Step 1: install.sh -->
      <div class="glass-card p-7 ring-cy-300/15">
        <span class="text-[13px] font-extrabold tracking-[0.15em] text-cy-300">01</span>
        <h3 class="mt-1 text-[20px] font-bold tracking-tight">Install on your Mac</h3>
        <div class="mt-5 rounded-xl bg-black p-4 ring-1 ring-white/5">
          <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-cy-300">$ ./install.sh</code>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-5 text-[13px] leading-[1.55] text-mute-fg">
          Build, sign with your Apple Developer cert, install the menu bar app and
          LaunchAgent, set up the system permissions. Idempotent — re-run any time.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 2: QR -->
      <div class="glass-card p-7 ring-cy-400/20">
        <span class="text-[13px] font-extrabold tracking-[0.15em] text-cy-400">02</span>
        <h3 class="mt-1 text-[20px] font-bold tracking-tight">Scan the QR</h3>
        <div class="mt-5 grid h-32 w-32 place-items-center rounded-xl bg-white p-3 mx-auto">
          <!-- Stylised QR — purely decorative -->
          <svg viewBox="0 0 110 110" class="h-full w-full" aria-hidden="true">
            <rect x="0" y="0" width="32" height="32" fill="#000"/>
            <rect x="6" y="6" width="20" height="20" fill="#fff"/>
            <rect x="12" y="12" width="8" height="8" fill="#000"/>
            <rect x="78" y="0" width="32" height="32" fill="#000"/>
            <rect x="84" y="6" width="20" height="20" fill="#fff"/>
            <rect x="90" y="12" width="8" height="8" fill="#000"/>
            <rect x="0" y="78" width="32" height="32" fill="#000"/>
            <rect x="6" y="84" width="20" height="20" fill="#fff"/>
            <rect x="12" y="90" width="8" height="8" fill="#000"/>
            {/* random dots */}
            {[[45,15],[60,30],[42,50],[68,58],[40,68],[54,75],[68,82],[80,55],[50,90]].map(([x,y]) => (
              <rect x={x} y={y} width="8" height="8" fill="#000"/>
            ))}
          </svg>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-5 text-[13px] leading-[1.55] text-mute-fg">
          Click the menu bar icon → Pair phone. Open Page on iPhone and point the
          camera at the QR. Pairing token never leaves your network.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 3: walk away -->
      <div class="glass-card p-7 ring-kind-idle/20">
        <span class="text-[13px] font-extrabold tracking-[0.15em] text-kind-idle">03</span>
        <h3 class="mt-1 text-[20px] font-bold tracking-tight">Walk away</h3>
        <div class="mt-5 rounded-xl bg-ink-800 p-3.5">
          <div class="font-mono text-[10px] text-mute-fg">mac-on-claude-code</div>
          <div class="mt-1.5 flex items-center gap-1.5">
            <span class="chip-kind text-kind-approval ring-kind-approval">APPROVAL</span>
            <span class="pill-backend text-brand-codex ring-brand-codex/55 bg-brand-codex/15">
              <span class="font-extrabold">CODEX</span><span class="font-medium opacity-90">CLI</span>
            </span>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-[11px] font-bold">Run this command?</p>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-5 text-[13px] leading-[1.55] text-mute-fg">
          Start your agent and step out. The moment something needs a human, your phone
          lights up. Reply with the same intent you'd type at the keyboard.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
